{"ID": 54771, "name": "Drye v. United States", "href": "https://api.oyez.org/cases/1999/98-1101", "view_count": 0, "docket_number": "98-1101", "timeline": [{"event": "Argued", "dates": [942040800], "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_timeline/case_timeline/38297"}, {"event": "Decided", "dates": [944546400], "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_timeline/case_timeline/38298"}], "question": "<p>Does an heir's interest to an estate constitute \"property\" or \"rights to property\" such that federal liens are valid against the heir's interest, even if the heir has disclaimed the interest under state law?</p>\n", "citation": {"volume": "528", "page": "49", "year": "1999", "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_citation/case_citation/18700"}, "term": "1999", "description": null, "justia_url": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/528/49/"}